<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1502,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,351,1502,1529]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Taxonomic note:</emphasis>
The genus comprises 14 species distributed throughout the Oriental tropics including Indo-Burmese and Sundaland hotspot regions to the 
<collectingCountry box="[630,759,1539,1565]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, with maximum diversity from the Borneo (
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[1246,1424,1539,1565]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">Holloway 2001</bibRefCitation>
). From 
<collectingCountry box="[219,279,1575,1601]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">India</collectingCountry>
, five species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[461,578,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[461,578,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Garudinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are hitherto known with only one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1863)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[1062,1374,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulana">
<emphasis box="[1062,1199,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">G. simulana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[1214,1366,1575,1601]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 561" refId="ref11513" refString="Walker, F. (1863) List of the specimens of Lepidopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum. Crambites &amp; Tortricites. Part 28. Edward Newman, London, pp. 1 - 561." type="book chapter" year="1863">Walker, 1863</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Great Nicobar Island (
<bibRefCitation author="Arora, G. S. &amp; Singh, A. K." box="[440,673,1610,1637]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="6 - 7" refId="ref8264" refString="Arora, G. S. &amp; Singh, A. K. (1975) A short note on some new records of Lithosiinae moths (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae) from Great Nicobar Island. Newsletter Zoological Survey of India, 1 (1), 6 - 7." type="journal article" year="1975">Arora &amp; Singh 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Singh, N. &amp; Joshi, R. &amp; Kirti, J. S. &amp; Bisht, S. S. &amp; Param, H. S." box="[684,891,1611,1637]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="1" refId="ref10678" refString="Singh, N., Joshi, R., Kirti, J. S., Bisht, S. S. &amp; Param, H. S. (2021 e) A catalogue of Indian Arctiinae (Erebidae, Lepidoptera). Zootaxa, 5058 (1), 001 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5058.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Singh 
<emphasis box="[756,812,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">et al.</emphasis>
2021e
</bibRefCitation>
). Externally, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[1151,1268,1611,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1151,1268,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Garudinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore, 1882" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[204,449,1647,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Padenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[204,297,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Padenia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[304,449,1647,1673]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="72 - 143" refId="ref10016" refString="Moore, F. (1882) The Lepidoptera of Ceylon. Vol. II. L. Reeve &amp; CO., London, 162 pp., pls. 72 - 143." type="book chapter" year="1882">Moore, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and shares the similar looking forewing pattern comprising whitish or ochreous ground colour with two blackish-brown bands on it, and marginally excised hindwing in males. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[1274,1391,1683,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1274,1391,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Garudinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has broader bands with often basal or subbasal bands not touching the costa of forewing and the hindwing is mostly shaded with grey or fuscous. The androconial patches in males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[920,1013,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Padenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[920,1013,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Padenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to the hindwing costa, whereas, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[287,404,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[287,404,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Garudinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they are found in the cell of forewing and sometimes in the cell and near the apex of hindwing as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[277,415,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulana">
<emphasis box="[277,415,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">G. simulana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. In male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1882" box="[797,914,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Garudinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[797,914,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Garudinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinct by the presence of a typical short, slender and curved distal part to the well-developed saccular process of the valva.
</paragraph>
